      • onDeviceInfoReceived

        void onDeviceInfoReceived(java.util.Hashtable<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> paramHashtable)
        Callback for SPDeviceController.getDeviceInfo()

        Return the device information.

        Parameters:
        paramHashtable - hashtable key and value.

        SPDeviceController.DI_BATTERYLEVEL : Battery voltage
        SPDeviceController.DI_BATTERYPERCENT : Battery percentage
        SPDeviceController.DI_BID : Spectra POS ID
        SPDeviceController.DI_PRODUCTID : Product ID
        SPDeviceController.DI_SERIALNUMBER : Serial number of the device
        SPDeviceController.DI_VENDERID : Vendor ID
        SPDeviceController.DI_HWVERSION : Hardware version
        SPDeviceController.DI_FMVERSION : Firmware version
        SPDeviceController.DI_ISCHARGING : True if device is charging
        SPDeviceController.DI_ISSUPPORTTRK1 : True if MSR Track1 support
        SPDeviceController.DI_ISSUPPORTTRK2 : True if MSR Track2 support
        SPDeviceController.DI_ISSUPPORTTRK3 : True if MSR Track3 support
        SPDeviceController.DI_ISSUPPORTNFC : True if NFC support
        SPDeviceController.DI_ISUSBCONNECTED : True if USB connected
